results.description: Come join your fellow LI Developers for a night of coding. - Your welcome to come hack on anything! Any language, framework, public/open-source, personal, etc. - Have an idea but don't know where to start? Sprint nights provide a great opportunity to connect with other developers, ask questions and get feedback. - Don't have a project your interested in? You're more than welcome to come and try to pair up with someone - Hook up to the projector and show off your work - Light snacks will be available - Drop in and bounce out whenever you need to
results.name: April Sprint Night

results.description:
Our social meetups are always a blast! Come join us for some apps, drinks and great discussion. Help inspire some of that great conversation by posting some interesting articles or podcasts you've come across below so that we can share opinions and ideas! Please RSVP so we can ensure we have a space large enough to accommodate our group!

We are going to go checkout Brownstone Brewing (http://brownstonebrewing.com/), Tuesdays they offer Taps and Apps, $3 off Beer & Apps.
results.name: April Social Meetup & Happy Hour

results.description:
INTRO TO REDUX

This month, we will be updating our React app from our "Intro to React' presentations to utilize Redux for state management.

We will cover domain state, form state and when to choose React's local state vs. Redux for UI state. We will also go over the basic functionality of the Redux Dev Tools.

You can find the source code for the completed React project here:
https://github.com/gojutin/buzzwords

Please feel free to bring your laptops if you would like to follow along. You will want to have Node.js installed on your computer along with the Chrome browser and your code editor of choice.

See you all next Wednesday!
results.name: JavaScript Monthly Meetup- Intro to Redux

results.description:
Theme: Social Media Marketing and SEO

Discussion Topic: Social Media Marketing Success and Failures

Discussion Topic: SEO Tips and Tricks

Call for Presenters: Want to do a deep dive on the topic? Let me know, we'd love to have you speak! Otherwise I'm prepared to talk a bit about my experiences promoting LI Kick
results.name: May Presentation Night: Social Media Marketing & SEO

results.description:
Our monthly Meetup will cover all things JavaScript, from plain JavaScript to JavaScript frameworks and libraries.

The Meetup will be divided into two segments:

1. Beginner (6:00-7:30 PM)

• During this time, we will primarily focus on the fundamental concepts of JavaScript.

• We will also cover the basics of popular JavaScript libraries, including jQuery and Node.js.

• Make sure to RSVP and bring your laptops! We will be working through several code examples.

• At this time, food will not be provided. Please make sure to eat in advance or feel free to bring food. There are also several great restaurants located within walking distance.

2. Advanced (7:30-9:00 PM)

• During this time, we will focus on more advanced concepts in JavaScript and JavaScript libraries.

We will post the agenda for this Meetup closer to the scheduled date.

Looking forward to seeing you there!

- Justin
